<h3 id="add-social-sharing-buttons">Add social sharing buttons</h3>

<p>Simply add the following line anywhere in your markdown:</p>

<pre><code>
{% include sharing.html %}

</code></pre>
<h3 id="font-awesome-is-also-included">Font awesome is also included</h3>

<p><i class="fa fa-quote-left fa-3x fa-pull-left fa-border"></i> Now you can use all the cool icons you want! <a href="http://fontawesome.io">Font Awesome</a> is indeed awesome. But wait, you don‚Äôt need this sweetness and you don‚Äôt want that little bit of load time from the font awesome css? No problem, just disable it in the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">config.yml</code> file, and it won‚Äôt be loaded.</p>

<ul class="fa-ul">
  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square"></i>you can make lists...</li>
  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>with cool icons like this,</li>
  <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i>even ones that move!</li>
</ul>

<p>If you need them, you can stick any of the <a href="http://fontawesome.io/icons/">605 icons</a> anywhere, with any size you like. (<a href="http://fontawesome.io/examples/">See documentation</a>)</p>

